As of the April 2010 census, the population of Colorado Springs was 416,427&lt;ref&gt;http://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Colorado_stplace2.html&lt;/ref&gt; ([[list of United States cities by population|47th most populous U.S. city]]),&lt;ref name=popest&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/popest/cities/files/SUB-EST2008-8.csv|title=Incorporated Places and Minor Civil Divisions: Coorado|format=CSV|year=2009|work=2008 Population Estimates|author=U.S. Census Bureau |authorlink=United States Census Bureau |accessdate=September 21, 2009}}&lt;/ref&gt; and the estimated population of the [[Colorado Springs Metropolitan Statistical Area]] was 617,714 in 2008 ([[United States metropolitan area|84th most populous MSA]]),&lt;ref name=msaest&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/popest/metro/CBSA-est2008-pop-chg.html |title=Estimates of Population Change for Metropolitan Statistical Areas and Rankings: July&amp;nbsp;1, 2007 to 1&amp;nbsp;July 2008 |publisher=Census.gov |date= |accessdate=October 5, 2009}}&lt;/ref&gt; and the population of the [[Front Range Urban Corridor]] in Colorado was an estimated 4,166,855.

April 2010 census:&lt;ref&gt;http://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Colorado_stplace2.html&lt;/ref&gt;

