===Eponyms===
Claude Debussy's name has, posthumously, been given to a number of discoveries. These include:
*[[Debussy Heights]], a heights at Ravel Peak which was discovered in 1960;
*[[Debussy (crater)|Debussy]], an [[impact crater]] on [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]] which was discovered in 1969;
*[[4492 Debussy]], a [[asteroid belt|main belt]] [[asteroid]] which was discovered in 1988.

===Recordings===
Debussy participated in a handful of recordings, made in 1904, with soprano [[Mary Garden]]. He also made some piano rolls for [[Welte Mignon]] in 1913.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://homepage.mac.com/stevepur/music/debussy_plays.html |title=Steve's Debussy Page |publisher=Homepage.mac.com |date=1913-11-01 |accessdate=2010-03-10}}&lt;/ref&gt;

